# Routing & Navigation

## App Router Structure
This project uses Next.js 15 App Router with the following structure:

```
app/
├── layout.tsx                 # Root layout
├── globals.css               # Global styles
├── (pages)/                  # Route group for main pages
│   ├── layout.tsx           # Pages layout
│   ├── (home)/              # Home page route group
│   │   └── page.tsx         # Home page component
│   ├── about/               # About page
│   │   └── page.tsx
│   └── projects/            # Projects section
│       ├── page.tsx         # Projects listing
│       └── [id]/            # Dynamic project pages
│           └── page.tsx
```

## Navigation Patterns
- **Sidebar Navigation**: Main navigation in [components/app-sidebar.tsx](mdc:components/app-sidebar.tsx)
- **Route Groups**: Use `(pages)` to organize routes without affecting URL structure
- **Dynamic Routes**: Use `[id]` for dynamic project pages

## Page Component Structure
Each page should follow this pattern:

```typescript
// app/(pages)/example/page.tsx
export default function ExamplePage() {
  return (
    <div className="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12">
      <div className="space-y-6">
        {/* Page content */}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Metadata Configuration
- Set page metadata using Next.js `metadata` export
- Configure in layout files for section-wide metadata
- Use dynamic metadata for dynamic routes

## Link Patterns
- Use Next.js `Link` component for internal navigation
- Implement active states in sidebar navigation
- Use proper `href` attributes for accessibility

## Layout Hierarchy
1. **Root Layout** ([app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx)) - Theme, fonts, sidebar provider
2. **Pages Layout** ([app/(pages)/layout.tsx](mdc:app/(pages)/layout.tsx)) - Content-specific layout
3. **Page Components** - Individual page content

## Sidebar Navigation Structure
The sidebar includes:
- Home link
- About section
- Projects section with collapsible items
- External links (GitHub, LinkedIn, etc.)
- Theme toggle

## URL Structure
- `/` - Home page
- `/about` - About page  
- `/projects` - Projects listing
- `/projects/[id]` - Individual project pages
